<item>
            <title>[SPARK-4606] SparkSubmitDriverBootstrapper does not propagate EOF to child JVM</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-4606</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Run this with &quot;spark.driver.extraJavaOptions&quot; set in your spark-defaults.conf:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;  echo &quot;&quot; | spark-shell --master local -Xnojline
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;You&apos;ll end up with a child process that cannot read from stdin (you can CTRL-C out of it though). That&apos;s because when the bootstrapper&apos;s stdin reaches EOF, that is not propagated to the child JVM that&apos;s actually doing the reading.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
